# FinTracker-Vault — development guidelines (persistent)

Use this as **baseline context** for any feature work. Full detail lives in repo docs (do not duplicate long playbooks here).

## Canonical docs (read when planning or scaffolding)

| Doc | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) | Agent/developer entry: invariants, app ports, links |
| [`CLAUDE.md`](../../CLAUDE.md) | Architecture, env, deployment, **Developer and agent playbook** (new apps, pages, API caching, shared UI) |
| [`.cursor/rules/google-oauth-env.mdc`](./google-oauth-env.mdc) | Google client ID / allowlist env names — **do not invent new keys** |
| [`.cursor/rules/git-pr-only-main.mdc`](./git-pr-only-main.mdc) | **Git:** PR-only updates to `main` — **no direct push** |

## Non-negotiables

- **Git / `main`:** Use a **branch + PR** for every change; **do not push commits directly to `main`**. See [`.cursor/rules/git-pr-only-main.mdc`](./git-pr-only-main.mdc).
- Run **`pnpm type-check`** at repo root before pushing (`.git/hooks/pre-push`).
- **Global CSS** only in `src/pages/_app.tsx` or `_document.tsx` — not in page components.
- **Imports** across packages: `@fintracker-vault/*` aliases from root `tsconfig.json`.
- **New Next apps**: `packages/apps/resolve-google-env.cjs` + **`getGoogleAuthEnv(__dirname)`** in `next.config.js`; list all consumed packages in **`transpilePackages`**; mirror **`experimental.outputFileTracingRoot`** from existing apps.
- **Shared UI** (`@fintracker-vault/ui`): after editing `packages/shared/ui/src`, run **`pnpm --filter @fintracker-vault/ui run build`** so consumers see updated `dist/`.
- **Shared auth** (`@fintracker-vault/auth`): after editing `packages/shared/auth/src`, run **`pnpm --filter @fintracker-vault/auth run build`**; list **`@fintracker-vault/auth`** in **`transpilePackages`**. **`middleware.ts`** should import from **`@fintracker-vault/auth/middleware`** (separate entry) so the Edge bundle does not include **`jose`**.
- **Staff / GAS API pattern**: GET caching + **`invalidateCache`** on mutations — see `packages/apps/staff/src/api.ts` and **`CLAUDE.md`** playbook.

## New work quick checklist

- **New page**: `src/pages/…`, match app layout classes, no global CSS imports in the page file.
- **New API reads/writes**: default cache on reads; invalidate affected GET keys after writes (prefer encapsulation inside `api` methods).
- **New `appKind` for `AppAuthGate`**: update `packages/shared/ui` (`AppAuthGate`, icons, copy).

Prefer extending **`CLAUDE.md`** / **`AGENTS.md`** for new conventions instead of scattering one-off root markdown files.
